% ===========================================================================
% references.bib
%
% Bibliography for paper.tex. Every entry is referenced in at least one
% section_*.tex file (or paper.tex); grep for the key before removing.
%
% All entries verified against publisher/library records (Crossref, JSTOR,
% DataCite, OpenLibrary, publisher pages) in July 2026. Citation keys are
% kept stable even where the verified year differs from the key (e.g.
% fajgelbaumredding2018 published 2022; whitaker2013 published 1954), so
% that in-text \citep / \citet calls never break.
%
% AEA replication-package note: entries flagged with a "% DATA CITATION"
% comment are the formal citations for external data sources (IPUMS, INDEC
% censuses, Larkin Plan, Baumgartner & Palazzo, ACA maps, IGN, FAO-GAEZ,
% USGS GTOPO30) and must also appear in the replication README's data
% availability statement. The flag lives in comments (not note fields) so
% it does not render in the compiled References.
% ===========================================================================

